HEADWORD: Paleichthyes
<hw>Pa`le*ich"thy*es</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Paleo-</er>, and <er>Ichthyology</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A comprehensive division of fishes which includes the elasmobranchs
and ganoids.</def> <altsp>[Written also
